<img class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-32449" src="http://www.nta.ng/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/air-force-420x312.jpg" alt="" width="420" height="312" srcset="http://www.nta.ng/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/air-force-420x312.jpg 420w, http://www.nta.ng/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/air-force-150x112.jpg 150w, http://www.nta.ng/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/air-force-160x119.jpg 160w, http://www.nta.ng/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/air-force.jpg 546w" sizes="(max-width: 420px) 100vw, 420px" /> The Nigerian Air Force (NAF) says the Air Task Force (ATF) of Operation LAFIYA DOLE has neutralised several Islamic State of West Africa Province (ISWAP) fighters at their hideout near Baga in Northern Borno. NAF Director of Public Relations and Information, Air Commodore Ibikunle Daramola, who disclosed this in a statement on Sunday in Abuja, said the operation was carried out on Saturday. He explained that the attack was conducted after a NAF Intelligence, Surveillance and Reconnaissance (ISR) platform spotted the terrorists assembled under some trees around the Fish Dam near Baga. Daramola said the ATF therefore, dispatched an Alpha Jet aircraft to attack the location. ” The aircraft multiple attacks pass, killing several of the terrorists and causing serious injuries to others. “The surviving terrorists were mopped-up in subsequent follow-on strikes,” the spokesman said. (NAN) Currently in Social Media platform of NTA, Largest TV in Africa. Iam a graduate of Mass Communication with special interest on social media and Online Editor and a Reporter.